c Production Course Integration — Task Graph\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer — Task Graph\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Generated:** 2026-04-16T05:42:58.472070+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Total tasks:** 25\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Estimated effort:** ~90 hours\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Generated:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.335643+00:00\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Total tasks:** 40\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Estimated effort:** ~129 hours\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n@@ -10,46 +10,72 @@\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 1 | T-001 | Add dynamics, compression, sidechain, and deference policy. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-010 | — | - production profile maps arc phase to dynamic range, compression intensity, transient policy, and sidechain/deference rules<br/>- Theramini and environmental transients can request generated-material ducking or silence<br/>- tests verify dynamic targets, sidechain metadata, and no over-compression in Divination/Crystallization |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 2 | T-002 | Add spatial, reverb, and delay production profiles. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-011 | — | - phase profiles define stereo width, near/far depth, reverb size/decay/damping, delay style, and transition-space behavior<br/>- tracker scenes expose spatial intent and reverb/delay sends<br/>- tests verify wide sparse openings, clearer Conversation space, focused Convergence, and long Crystallization tails |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 3 | T-003 | Complete mastering and loudness policy for installation playback. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-012 | — | - master policy targets installation-safe LUFS/peak ranges, limiter ceiling, broad EQ intent, and phase-specific dynamic contrast<br/>- automated proxies catch clipping, silence, harshness, and low-end runaway<br/>- tests verify master profiles and synthetic render/loudness proxies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 4 | T-004 | Implement critical-listening and psychoacoustic interpretation rules. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-013 | — | - ear engine or production evaluator exposes spectral balance, dynamic contour, spatial distribution, timbral quality, rhythmic activity, harmonic tension, masking risk, and equal-loudness compensation hints<br/>- feedback can modify future density, register, EQ, dynamics, and sound-palette choices<br/>- tests use synthetic events/audio features to verify correction decisions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 5 | T-005 | Encode SenseWeave voice-to-music interpretation rules. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-014 | — | - room, membrane/contact mic, garden, Theramini, archive, and network sources have musical mappings for pitch, rhythm, density, harmony, timbre, mix, and deference<br/>- Perform-VE condenser/room mic fallback is represented as a source option<br/>- tests verify quiet/noisy room, rain/wind/contact vibration, garden inactivity, Theramini activity, archive recall, and network/weather mappings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 6 | T-006 | Implement ensemble-space and Theramini partner behavior from the course. | T1 | 3 | 3 | MPC-015 | — | - policy supports listening first, complementary register, rhythmic sympathy, harmonic response intervals, accompaniment textures, call/response, imitation, commentary, completion, and silence<br/>- score/tracker metadata identifies current lead/support roles<br/>- tests verify no register crowding, no excessive overlap during human/Theramini gesture, and recovery to solo mode |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 7 | T-007 | Add a genre-literacy strategy library. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-016 | — | - strategies exist for ambient/drone/generative, minimalism, jazz, IDM/electronic, classical/orchestral form, musique concrete/electroacoustic, spectral music, blues, world-music concepts, and post-rock/experimental builds<br/>- strategies can influence form, harmony, rhythm, synthesis, arrangement, and mix without hardcoding imitation<br/>- tests verify strategy selection, arc affinity, and no missing required genre strategy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 8 | T-008 | Make the 30-minute production score executable. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-017 | — | - procedural arc exposes per-phase density, dynamic, harmonic, rhythm, timbre, spatial, compression, SenseWeave, and synthesis targets<br/>- score-tree commissioning and tracker compilation use those targets for long pieces and 5-minute proxy tests<br/>- tests verify the five-phase contour and phase-specific production metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 9 | T-009 | Add phase-transition composition techniques. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-018 | — | - transition planner supports pivot event, breath/silence, metric modulation, timbral morph, harmonic pivot chord, and common-tone bridge<br/>- adjacent sections share at least one continuity element unless a deliberate hard cut is tagged<br/>- tests verify no untagged abrupt phase jumps and valid transition metadata |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 1 total:** ~27 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 1 | T-001 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-010 | — | - CLI or Python API `ablate(score, seeds, disabled_rules=[...])` returns alternate PerformedPart<br/>- output includes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 2 | T-002 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-011 | — | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 3 | T-003 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-012 | — | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 4 | T-004 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-013 | — | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 5 | T-005 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-014 | — | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 6 | T-006 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-015 | — | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 7 | T-007 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-016 | — | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 8 | T-008 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-017 | — | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 9 | T-009 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-018 | — | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 10 | T-010 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-019 | — | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 1 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Sprint 3 — Improvement Engine Hardening\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Sprint 2 — Quality Scoring\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 10 | T-010 | Wire production-course choices into score trees and tracker output. | T1 | 3 | 3 | MPC-020 | — | - score trees carry production vocabulary for mode/scale, harmonic function, meter/groove, counterpoint relation, synthesis architecture, mix role, spatial intent, genre strategy, phase profile, and transition type<br/>- tracker scenes/steps preserve enough metadata for runtime scheduling and diagnostics<br/>- tests verify metadata survives compose -> gate -> compile -> schedule |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 11 | T-011 | Extend the composition gate with production-course checks. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-021 | — | - gate can reject phase-inappropriate density, missing harmonic/rhythm metadata, unsafe register, flat dynamics, missing transition continuity, missing mix role, and untagged genre/strategy choices for long pieces<br/>- intentionally sparse/micro pieces can pass when they carry valid sparse intent<br/>- tests cover both rejection and acceptance paths |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 12 | T-012 | Add end-to-end production-course integration tests. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-025 | — | - tests compose, gate, compile, schedule, and inspect a 5-minute proxy arc using production-course metadata<br/>- tests verify non-silent output proxy, no single-note long sections, phase contour, transition continuity, mix role allocation, and repertoire storage<br/>- tests run without live hardware and with mocked SenseWeave/Theramini inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 11 | T-011 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-030 | T-001 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 12 | T-012 | Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-031 | T-001 | - scheduler writes sensor_tempo_scale ∈ [0.92, 1.08], sensor_amp_scale ∈ [0.80, 1.20], sensor_brightness ∈ [-1.0, +1.0] onto each Event<br/>- delta track is persisted as JSON alongside audio output for replay<br/>- out-of-bounds values clamped and logged<br/>- tests verify clamping, persistence, and replay consumes the delta track |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 13 | T-013 | Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-033 | T-001 | - `operator_diagnostics.py` extended with aggregate_intentions block<br/>- raw sensor values are NOT surfaced alongside synth parameters in diagnostics (prevents accidentally re-introducing gimmicky reverse-mappings)<br/>- tests verify telemetry shape and absence of raw pairings |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 14 | T-014 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-034 | T-001 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 15 | T-015 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-035 | T-001 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 16 | T-016 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-036 | T-001 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 17 | T-017 | Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-037 | T-001 | - pytest gate runs metrics on a curated fixture set of 5-minute rendered pieces<br/>- any metric outside pass band or any anti-pattern trigger fails the build<br/>- pass bands are per-intent-tag where applicable (withhold-tagged phrases allow lower velocity σ)<br/>- tests verify a deliberately broken render fails the gate and a healthy render passes |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 18 | T-018 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-039 | T-001 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 3 total:** ~9 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 2 total:** ~24 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n ---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-## Sprint 5 — Library & CRUD Polish\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Sprint 3 — Improvement Engine Hardening\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 13 | T-013 | Create a production-course knowledge base that the composer can consult at runtime. | T1 | 5 | 3 | MPC-001 | T-001 | - course concepts are represented as typed data or markdown references with stable IDs<br/>- arc-phase profiles exist for Divination, Emergence, Conversation, Convergence, and Crystallization<br/>- tests verify all required chapters/phase profiles are present and loadable |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 14 | T-014 | Implement a verified pitch, interval, scale, and mode library. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-002 | T-001 | - library includes chromatic, major/minor, seven modes, pentatonic, whole-tone, octatonic, blues, Hirajoshi, In Sen, Pelog, Bhairav, Hungarian minor, Prometheus, and microtonal/ratio helpers<br/>- interval metadata includes semitones, consonance/dissonance, character, and arc-phase affinity<br/>- tests verify interval/scale pitch-class sets and MIDI/frequency conversion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 15 | T-015 | Add chord construction and voicing support. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-003 | T-001 | - triads, seventh chords, extended chords, altered dominants, suspended/add chords, drop voicings, close/open voicings, and rootless/guide-tone voicings are supported<br/>- voicing engine respects register limits and configured spacing<br/>- tests verify chord pitch classes, unique voicings, range safety, and smooth voice-leading choices |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 16 | T-016 | Encode functional harmony and modulation strategies. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-004 | T-001 | - harmonic planner can label tonic, subdominant, dominant, secondary dominant, modal-interchange, tritone-sub, chromatic-mediant, pedal, planing, and modulation functions<br/>- score trees expose harmonic function and transition intent per section<br/>- tests verify cadence resolution, pivot/common-tone modulation continuity, and phase-appropriate tension levels |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 17 | T-017 | Expand rhythm, meter, groove, and time handling. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-005 | T-001 | - rhythm engine supports 4/4, 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8, free/rubato, swing, shuffle, dotted cells, push/pull, polyrhythm, polymeter, and metric modulation<br/>- tracker metadata carries meter, subdivision, swing ratio, groove timing, and phrase breath without breaking deterministic row scheduling<br/>- tests verify IOI ratios, swing offsets, polyrhythm cycle length, and phase-specific meter policies |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 18 | T-018 | Add counterpoint and linear voice-combination rules. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-006 | T-001 | - arrangement/compiler can choose contrary, oblique, parallel, echo, commentary, and completion relationships between lanes<br/>- dissonance and resolution rules are available as metadata checks<br/>- tests verify independent lane contours, staggered climaxes, and no accidental lane crowding |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 19 | T-019 | Build a synthesis-architecture strategy registry. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-008 | T-001 | - registry covers subtractive, FM, additive, granular, physical modeling, and spectral/FFT processing with safe parameter ranges and arc-phase affinities<br/>- score tree or tracker scenes can request synthesis architecture by production role<br/>- tests verify each architecture has role tags, macro controls, safe ranges, and fallbacks |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-| 20 | T-020 | Add production-aware frequency allocation and EQ policy. | T1 | 2 | 3 | MPC-009 | T-001 | - mix engine assigns sub, bass, low-mid, midrange, upper-mid, presence, and air lanes to roles<br/>- production metadata includes HPF/LPF/EQ intent for bass, pad, lead, texture, noise, sample, and Theramini lanes<br/>- tests verify role frequency lanes avoid primary masking and preserve bass center policy |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 19 | T-019 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | T1 | 7 | 3 | CCH-020 | T-011 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 20 | T-020 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-021 | T-011 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during score-tree → Event-list conversion<br/>- harmonic_charge uses tonal-pitch-space distance (Lerdahl) normalized 0..1<br/>- tests on known-score fixtures verify expected feature values |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 21 | T-021 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-022 | T-011 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 22 | T-022 | Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-023 | T-011 | - `render/rules/silence_budget.py` maintains rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density)·dt per voice<br/>- when rest_budget exceeds threshold at phrase boundary, either extends breath (via R6) or drops next phrase to tacet<br/>- tests verify accumulator math, threshold trigger, and tacet-drop path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 23 | T-023 | Implement wind/voice lung-capacity constraints: 4–8 s continuous-play cap per instrument-sim voice. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-024 | T-011 | - voices with lung_capacity set (default 6 s for winds/voice, null for others) track continuous sounding time<br/>- exceeding cap forces a breath at next phrase boundary or earlier if density tolerates<br/>- tests verify cap enforcement and breath insertion |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 24 | T-024 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-025 | T-011 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 25 | T-025 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-026 | T-011 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 26 | T-026 | Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-027 | T-011 | - swing ratio computed from current tempo rather than fixed global setting<br/>- short-note duration held near 100 ms across tempo range<br/>- optional role-specific override (cymbal uses ride ratio, soloists use Benadon BUR 1.2–1.7)<br/>- tests verify ratio curve and short-note invariance |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 27 | T-027 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-028 | T-011 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 28 | T-028 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-029 | T-011 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+**Sprint 3 total:** ~30 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+---\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-**Sprint 5 total:** ~24 hrs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+## Sprint 5 — Library & CRUD Polish\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+|-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 29 | T-029 | Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-001 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines Event with event_id, phrase_id, section_id, voice_id, role, pitch, nominal_beat, nominal_dur_beats, harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, is_phrase_start/end, is_cadential, intent_tag, onset_sec, dur_sec, velocity, timing_deviation_ms, articulation, sensor_tempo_scale, sensor_amp_scale, sensor_brightness, rule_stack (list[str]), seed_path (tuple[int, ...])<br/>- score-level fields are immutable after render stage<br/>- dataclass is JSON-serializable and round-trips through OSC bundle encoding<br/>- unit tests verify field presence, immutability of score-level fields, and serialization round-trip |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 30 | T-030 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-002 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 31 | T-031 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-003 | T-001 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 32 | T-032 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-004 | T-001 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 33 | T-033 | Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-005 | T-001 | - Role enum exists with grid_locked boolean attribute (ostinato=True, perc=True, melody=False, pad=False, accent=False, silence=N/A)<br/>- every rule in the stack respects a shared `rule.applies_to(role)` filter so grid-locked voices skip R1–R8<br/>- tests verify grid-locked voices emerge from the render pass with timing_deviation_ms == 0 and no microtiming jitter |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 34 | T-034 | Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-006 | T-001 | - `render/seed.py` exposes derive_seed(root_seed, path_tuple) returning deterministic 32-bit sub-seed<br/>- Event.seed_path records the exact path used so any randomness inside rules can be reproduced<br/>- tests verify same (root, path) always yields same sub-seed across process restarts and Python minor versions |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 35 | T-035 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-007 | T-001 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+| 36 | T-036 | Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-008 | T-001 | - OSCend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Brought the gallery back under the same AV boot contract as the face: the repo now ships a top-level `gallery_x11.py` entrypoint again, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now starts and deduplicates `gallery_x11.py` alongside `face_display.py` so reboot recovery cannot leave the gallery unmanaged or multiplied into dozens of stale X processes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Tightened the display recovery behavior again: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` on recovery instead of only deduplicating them, because a single stale headless display process was enough to leave the monitors blank while still looking “healthy” in `ps`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Fixed the display-runtime environment for those restarts too: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now exports `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000` before launching face and gallery, which avoids the live SDL/X error where both display clients would restart with `DISPLAY=:0` but still fail to attach to the user session.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Hardened the sample-playback daemon so stable ambient scenes can refresh repeatedly after cooldown instead of firing once per unchanged signature, and render failures now write a structured error state instead of crashing the loop.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Taught `face_display.py` to surface the live EMSD sample layer from `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json`, so the head monitor can show which source and activity mode the room-sampling layer is currently holding or triggering.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n+- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visitests/test_first_boot.py:444:        identity = bootstrap_identity(identity_path=path)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:5358:| 21 | T-021 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-022 | T-011 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:5474:  - `render/rules/` — one module per R-rule (metric_accent.py, phrase_arch.py, agogic.py, duration_contrast.py, final_rit.py, punctuation.py, articulation.py, microtiming.py, motif_memory.py, silence_budget.py, call_response.py, sensor_intent.py)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-001_20260416T181925Za_1776378511.log:5513:| CCH-022 | Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home |\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Z_1776393558.log:11:- `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-021_20260416T181925Z_1776393558.log:41:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"message\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"2026-04-17T02:39:22.519Z\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"role\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"user\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"<!--\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  sdp-cli agent-specific template for gemini\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  Edit this file to tune how gemini handles lead_t1.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  The shipped default lives at src/sdp/prompts/templates/lead_t1.md.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  Delete this file to revert to the default.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n-->\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n# Task T-021@20260416T181925Z: Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Acceptance Criteria\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `render/rules/motif_memory.py` hashes motifs by pitch-class + rhythm signature<br/>- on hash match, select variation from {transposition, inversion, retrograde, rhythmic augmentation, re-voicing, partial fragmentation} weighted inversely by recency<br/>- cache decays so original motif reappears every ~8 iterations<br/>- tests verify variation selection, recency weighting, and return-home\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n**Tier:** T1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Instructions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Read the failing test or bug report to understand the core issue.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Make the minimal code change required to fix the problem.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Run the relevant tests to confirm the fix and ensure no regressions were introduced.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n4. Commit the change with a clear commit message: `fix(scope): summary [T-021@20260416T181925Z]`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not expand scope; address only the reported problem.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Follow existing code style and patterns.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Do not clean, revert, commit, or otherwise normalize unrelated pre-existing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  workspace changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Commit your working change immediate