\\nAll R1–R8 rules are covered. Integration and gate tests in `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py` exhaustively verify that melodic roles are shaped while grid-locked roles (like `ostinato`) remain exactly quantized and unmutated. Identity persistence is verified by `tests/test_first_boot.py`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Consistency\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe shared contract follows established patterns in the render pipeline. Rule IDs (R1–R8) are consistently applied and mapped to their respective implementations. The use of `role_is_eligible` provides a single point of truth for gating logic.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Security\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNo security vulnerabilities or leaked secrets were found. Identity preservation follows the existing file-based persistence model.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Quality\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe code is well-structured and follows the project's architectural standards. The integration tests provide high confidence in the behavioral correctness of the gating mechanism.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Issues Found\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- None.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Verdict: PASS\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe implementation is solid and meets all acceptance criteria. The addition of `tests/test_role_gate_integration.py` is a valuable regression anchor for the render pipeline.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\\\\\\\\n./sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260416T054258Z_1776356839.log:- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\\\\\\\\n./sdp/templates/candidates/v